    • Field Detail

      • goalX

        int goalX
        End position of pointer move on X axis. By default it equals GamePlayController.pointerX, but in #PointerMoveAnimation(Move, StepCause) constructor} it's changed by move value.

      • goalY

        int goalY
        End position of pointer move on Y axis. By default it equals GamePlayController.pointerY, but in constructor it's changed by move value.

      • MOVE_SPEED

        final int MOVE_SPEED
        Speed (pixels/frame) of pointer movement. It can be only a multiple of 3 or 5, and also it can equal 1.

        public void handle(long now)
        This method needs to be overridden by extending classes. It is going to be called in every frame while the AnimationTimer is active.
        Specified by:
        handle in class ExtendedAnimationTimer
        Parameters:
        now - The timestamp of the current frame given in nanoseconds. This value will be the same for all AnimationTimers called during one frame.

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Overrides method ExtendedAnimationTimer.stop(). Why I have chosen to override? That's because of GamePlayController.movingPointer. This method is called many times, and I don't wanted to type such code: 
        
 movingPointer = false;
 stop();
 // return;
        Overrides:
        stop in class ExtendedAnimationTimer
